Hello,
in the new Lagrangian Kernel/Materials there may be a bug for the case large_kinematics = false. E.g., look at
void
ComputeStVenantKirchhoffStress::computeQpPK2Stress()
{
  ...
  if (_large_kinematics) // Large deformations = Green-Lagrange strain
    strain = _E[_qp];
  else // Small deformations = linear strain
    strain = 0.5 * (_F[_qp] + _F[_qp].transpose());      // <=====???=========================  

  // The stress update is linear with the correct strains/frame
  _S[_qp] = _C[_qp] * strain;
}

To my understanding the marked linearized strain computation should be replaced by something like
const RankTwoTensor I = RankTwoTensor::Identity();
RankTwoTensor H = _F[_qp] - I;   // displacement gradient
RankTwoTensor strain  = 0.5 * (H + H.transpose()); 

or put it in one line.
You can check that by setting large_kinematics = false (also in the [Materials] section)  in, e.g., the file
moose/modules/tensor_mechanics/test/tests/lagrangian//materials/correctness/stvenantkirchhoff.i
and set exodus = true. Then one observe in paraview a much too large deformation in comparison to the case large_kinematics = true.
The same problem applies to void ComputeNeoHookeanStress::computeQpPK2Stress()
Cheers

